Brunnsparken - Ronneby, Sweden

N 56° 11.978 E 015° 17.077

33V E 517659 N 6228334

Ronneby Brunnspark was named Sweden's most beautiful park in 2005.

Waymark Code: WM15T3A

Location: Blekinge, Sweden

Published By: pmaupin

Views: 0

Ronneby Brunnspark was named Sweden's most beautiful park in 2005.

It has its origins in the early 18th century, although its main infrastructure was created at the end of the 19th.

It can be visited for free all year round and consists of several different sections such as rose garden, Japanese garden, pergola and fragrance garden, lakes, fountains, picnic areas and more.

The park originally started as a health resort due to the very ferrous and healthy water. Many of the old buildings still exist and help to give the park its distinctive character.
